The paper discusses the use of machine learning for the detection of malware on Android platforms, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also involves the use of artificial intelligence techniques such as K-Nearest Neighbour classifier, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves the use of machine learning algorithms for classification, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the software engineering aspect of developing a detection system, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper involves the use of mobile devices, which falls under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
